ObservationTitle: Car strikes large boulder on rockfall-prone stretch of Seward Highway
ObservationSummary: No one was injured when a car hit a 6-foot-by-8-foot rock that fell from cliffs next to the Seward Highway late Wednesday.

ObservationTitle: Where's the snow? Warm weather to keep most of Eaglecrest closed this weekend
ObservationSummary: Night-time temperatures have been cold enough for snow but the snow quickly melts by morning.

ObservationTitle: For the first time, scientists have found a dangerous toxin from algae in the Bering Strait and Chukchi Sea
ObservationSummary: Clams collected in late August had concentrations of saxitoxin considered dangerous for human consumption. The samples were collected in August about 70 miles north of St. Lawrence Island and about 50 miles north of Cape Lisburne, much further north than previously documented.

ObservationTitle: Kipnuk the latest village to flood as storms rile the ice-free Bering Sea
ObservationSummary: This has become the new norm across the Yukon-Kuskokwim Delta. Late winters and sudden thawing have turned roads into slush and made rivers and sloughs, which are necessary for travel, less safe because they take longer to freeze.

ObservationTitle: In Sweden's Arctic, ice atop snow leaves reindeer starving
ObservationSummary: Hiila Inga is concerned about the health of his reindeer. His community herds 8000 head each year, between traditional grazing lands in the mountain and the forests further east.
